==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[impecuniosus]], [[in-]], ''not'' + [[pecunia]], ''money'' + [[-osus]], ''full of''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːniəs|-uːniəs]]

===Adjective===
'''impecunious'''

#lacking [[money]]
===Synonyms===
*[[poor]]
===Translations===

*Czech: [[nemající peníze, jsoucí bez peněz, jsoucí bez prostředků, nezámožný, chudý]]  
''See under [[poor]].''

===Example===
:When I, good friends, was called to the bar,
:I'd an appetite fresh and hearty,
:But I was, as many young [[barrister]]s are,
:An impecunious party.
:--[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W._S._Gilbert William S. Gilbert], ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trial_by_Jury Trial by Jury]''

